:::summary
Human physiology is the science of how the human body works — how its organs, tissues, and cells perform their functions and integrate their activities to sustain life. Where anatomy asks "what is there?", physiology asks "what does it do?" Together they give us a profound picture of the living body as a system of extraordinary complexity, elegance, and purposeful design — one that the Psalmist fittingly described as "fearfully and wonderfully made" (Psalm 139:14).
:::

